nism exists to disable expired accounts\n   (cron job, systemd timer, LDAP/AD policy, or privileged account mgmt tool)\n\n2. Confirm organizational account lifecycle policy defines expiration criteria:\n   - Maximum account age (typically 1 year for contractors, 2-3 years for govt)\n   - Inactivity threshold (e.g., 90 days no login = disable)\n   - Password expiration (PASS_MAX_DAYS <= 60 days per DoD baseline)\n\n3. Review evidence of expired account enforcement:\n   - Disabled account audit logs\n   - System administrator account review procedures\n   - LDAP/AD group policy objects (GPOs) for account expiration\n\n4. Test account expiration mechanism:\n   - Create test account with past expiration date\n   - Verify account is automatically disabled (cannot authenticate)\n\nEvidence to collect:\n- Account lifecycle management policy document\n- LDAP/AD account expiration policy (if applicable)\n- System administrator procedures for quarterly account review\n- Audit logs showing disabled expired accounts\n- List of current active accounts with expiration dates (chage -l output)\n\n[POTENTIAL FINDING] No automated expiration mechanism detected\nManual account review is required, increasing risk of expired account usage.\n\nDoD requires: Automated enforcement of account expiration (accounts disabled\nimmediately upon expiration, no manual intervention required)."},{"group_id_src":"V-264338","group_tree":[{"id":"V-264338","title":"SRG-APP-000705","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-264338","severity":"medium","group_title":"The web server must disable accounts when the accounts are no longer associated to a user.","rule_id_src":"SV-264338r984359_rule","rule_id":"SV-264338r984359","rule_version":"SRG-APP-000705-WSR-000110","rule_title":"The web server must disable accounts when the accounts are no longer associated to a user.","fix_text":"Configure the web server to disable accounts when the accounts are no longer associated to a user.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the web server is configured to disable accounts when the accounts are no longer associated to a user.\n\nIf the web server is not configured to disable accounts when the accounts are no longer associated to a user, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Web_Server_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disabling expired, inactive, or otherwise anomalous accounts supports the concepts of least privilege and least functionality which reduce the attack surface of the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-003628"],"reference_identifier":"2910","uuid":"0dd173e9-d4ce-4fe6-b84d-0a9b4c90226e","stig_uuid":"daafa65b-58f2-4b29-ad69-b6d6ee9d7e07","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 02/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_WebSRG_AnswerFile.xml\r\nKey Name: XO\r\nIndex: 2\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\nORGANIZATIONAL POLICY VERIFICATION REQUIRED: Verify orphaned account management.\n\nRequired Verification:\n1. Review accounts with last login > 90 days (potential orphans identified in Finding Details)\n2. Cross-reference with HR records - verify all accounts belong to current employees\n3. Validate organizational account review process:\n   - Frequency: At least quarterly\n   - Documentation: Review logs maintained\n   - Approvals: Manager sign-off on active accounts\n4. Verify separation procedures:\n   - HR departure notification to IT security\n   - Account disabled within 8 hours of separation\n   - Account deleted after retention period (typically 30-90 days)\n\nRemediation:\n1. Disable orphaned accounts immediately: passwd -l [username] OR usermod -L -e 1 [username]\n2. Establish automa