/README.select-wordlist lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root   30 Jun  4  2025 /usr/share/dict/words -> /etc/dictionaries-common/words lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root   16 Jan 20  2022 /usr/share/dict/words.pre-dictionaries-common -> american-english\n\nCHECK 5: Organizational Password Policy Documentation\n   Required evidence from ISSO/ISSM:\n   - System Security Plan (SSP) with password policy section\n   - Organizational security policy (password requirements)\n   - Password guidelines document (compromised password list usage)\n   - Evidence of NIST 800-63B compliance (breach corpus integration)\n\nCHECK 6: Evidence of Periodic Compromised Password List Updates\n   Manual verification required:\n   - Review update frequency of compromised password lists\n   - Verify integration with public breach databases (e.g., Have I Been Pwned)\n   - Check change logs for password policy updates\n   - Confirm organizational process for incorporating new compromised passwords\n\nSUMMARY:\nThis check requires organizational policy verification. Automated checks cannot determine:\n- Whether compromised password lists are actively maintained and updated\n- Integration with breach corpuses (NIST, Have I Been Pwned, etc.)\n- Organizational processes for password validation during account creation/updates\n\nSTATUS: Open - Organizational policy verification required by ISSO/ISSM.\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-264349","group_tree":[{"id":"V-264349","title":"SRG-APP-000850","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-264349","severity":"medium","group_title":"The web server must, for password-based authentication, store passwords using an approved salted key derivation function, preferably using a keyed hash.","rule_id_src":"SV-264349r984392_rule","rule_id":"SV-264349r984392","rule_version":"SRG-APP-000850-WSR-000230","rule_title":"The web server must, for password-based authentication, store passwords using an approved salted key derivation function, preferably using a keyed hash.","fi